&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Educational Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Possess an undergraduate degree in Law with a minimum achievement of an upper second-class honours (2:1) or its international equivalent, or have completed a degree of comparable standard that includes modules covering corporate law.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research Proficiency:&lt;/strong&gt; Demonstrated ability to conduct comprehensive research on various subjects, with a keen ability to stay abreast of changes within the legal landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Problem Solving Abilities:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong problem-solving skills essential for identifying and addressing compliance and financial crime issues, assessing risks, and proposing effective, practical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adaptability:&lt;/strong&gt; Must have the capacity to adapt to evolving regulatory frameworks and organisational priorities efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Time Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Proficient time management skills required to prioritise tasks and meet deadlines in a dynamic, fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication Skills:&lt;/strong&gt; Excellent verbal and written communication skills are crucial.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attention to Detail:&lt;/strong&gt; Must exhibit exceptional accuracy and attention to detail in all aspects of paperwork and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proactivity:&lt;/strong&gt; Should be proactive in identifying legal issues, risks, and potential liabilities, with a responsibility to report these findings to corporate attorneys.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cultural Competency:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to work effectively within an international team, spanning multiple time zones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industry Interest:&lt;/strong&gt; A strong interest in fintech, cryptocurrency, and/or banking is highly desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
